<sec>
<st>
Quotes</st>
<p>

Quigley, describing the rifle:
<indent level="1">

 <it>It’s a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../313/621313.xml">
lever-action</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../340/28340.xml">
single shot</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../111/547111.xml">
breech loader</link>.  Usual barrel length’s thirty inches.  This one has an extra four.  It’s converted to use a special forty-five caliber, hundred and ten grain metal cartridge, with a five-hundred forty grain paper patch bullet.  It’s fitted with <idea wordnetid="105833840" confidence="0.8">
<concept wordnetid="105835747" confidence="0.8">
<component wordnetid="105868954" confidence="0.8">
